// ============================================================
// EXERCISE:
//   1. Change the key: replace all A→C, E→G, C→Eb (C minor)
//      Notice how different the same progression feels in a new key
//   2. Try the progression i–VII–VI–VII: Am–G–F–G
//      This "circular" progression never fully resolves — it loops
//   3. Change the melody to use only scale degrees 1, 3, 5 (A, C, E)
//      Does it feel more stable? Less interesting?
//   4. Listen to: Tale Of Us "Astral Me" — identify chord progression
//   5. Recondite "Hortus" — notice how melody and techno coexist
// ============================================================
